<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,593,1525,1551]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,358,1525,1551]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Gerbillus henleyi</emphasis>
(De Winton, 1903)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="42.[151,593,1525,1585]" box="[151,508,1560,1585]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,343,1560,1585]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Common name:</emphasis>
Pygmy gerbil.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="42" pageNumber="43" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="42.[151,1436,1632,1981]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,275,1632,1657]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Very small (hence pygmy) gerbil with small ears. White patches above eye and behind ear. Dorsal color buff brown, under parts are white, with a distinct line of demarcation (
<figureCitation box="[951,1066,1668,1693]" captionStart="FIGURE 47" captionStartId="43.[151,250,905,927]" captionTargetBox="[264,1323,193,884]" captionTargetId="figure@43.[264,1323,193,884]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURE 47. The pygmy gerbil, Gerbillus henleyi (photo by Mohammad Abu Baker)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202869/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Figure 47</figureCitation>
). Soles of hind feet naked. Skull small and delicate, with strongly inflated bullae. Braincase very broad, with short rostrum. Teeth very small and delicate (
<figureCitation box="[252,366,1740,1765]" captionStart="FIGURE 48" captionStartId="43.[151,250,1921,1943]" captionTargetBox="[264,1323,977,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@43.[264,1323,977,1900]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURE 48.A. Dorsal,B. Ventral views for the skull, and C. Upper maxillary teeth for Gerbillus henleyi." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202871/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Figure 48</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="42.[151,1436,1632,1981]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,536,1776,1801]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Localities: Previous records.</emphasis>
Al Jafr, Faidat Al Dhahik (
<bibRefCitation box="[839,1129,1776,1801]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" refId="ref31502" refString="Atallah, S. I. &amp; Harrison, D. L. (1967) New records of rodents, bats and insectivores from the Arabian Peninsula. Journal of Zoology, London, 153 (3), 311 - 319. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1469 - 7998.1967. tb 04065. x" type="journal article">Atallah &amp; Harrison, 1967</bibRefCitation>
); Al Hazīm, Al Jafr, Faydat ad Dahik, Ash Shawmarī (
<bibRefCitation box="[460,776,1812,1837]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" refId="ref30180" refString="Abu Baker, M. &amp; Amr, Z. (2003 a) A morphometric and taxonomic revision of the genus Gerbillus in Jordan with notes on its current distribution. Zoologische Abhandlungen (Dresden), 53, 177 - 204." type="journal article">Abu Baker &amp; Amr, 2003 a</bibRefCitation>
&amp; 
<bibRefCitation box="[819,836,1812,1837]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" refId="ref30224" refString="Abu Baker, M. &amp; Amr, Z. (2003 b) Rodent diversity in the Northeastern Desert of Jordan, with special reference on the ecology of Gerbillus cheesmani. (Mammalia: Rodentia). Casopis Narodniho Muzea, Rada prirodovedna, 172 (1 - 4), 141 - 152." type="journal article">b</bibRefCitation>
); Al Mudawwarah (Abu Baker &amp; Amr, 2004); Ash Shawmarī Wildlife Reserve (
<bibRefCitation box="[476,737,1848,1873]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" refId="ref30412" refString="Abu Baker, M., Qarqaz, M. &amp; Amr, Z. (2005) Small mammal remains recovered from pellets of the Barn Owl (Tyto alba) at Shawmari Wildlife Reserve, eastern Jordan. Casopis Narodniho Muzea, Rada prirodovedna, 174 (1 - 4), 12 7 - 129." type="journal article">
Abu Baker 
<emphasis box="[606,656,1848,1873]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">et al</emphasis>
., 2005
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[756,1076,1848,1873]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Materials from owl pellets.</emphasis>
Burqu' (Obuch, per. com.); Ash Shawmarī (Obuch, per. com.) (
<figureCitation box="[497,611,1884,1909]" captionStart="FIGURE 49" captionStartId="44.[151,250,1423,1445]" captionTargetBox="[275,1307,228,1368]" captionTargetId="figure@44.[264,1323,193,1401]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 49. Distribution of the pygmy gerbil, Gerbillus henleyi." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202873/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Figure 49</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="42" pageNumber="43" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="42.[151,1436,1632,1981]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,300,1920,1945]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Habitat:</emphasis>
Collected from Al Jafr area around cultivated fields (Atallah, 1978). This species prefers stony, gravelly falt deserts with ample vegetation. Its burrow is characterized by its small diameter (
<quantity box="[1196,1285,1957,1981]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" unit="cm" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2 cm</quantity>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
